entered nicaragua from costa rica 
last week the defense ministry accused rebel forces of making 
more than 140 attacks against nicaraguan military and civilian 
targets this year in open violation of the ceasefire 
the rebels radio station radio liberacion said saturday that 
sandinista troops had violated the ceasefire 69 times in 1989 
the sandinistas and rebels agreed to a temporary ceasefire in 
march 1988 but peace talks subsequently broke down the government 
then declared a monthly series of unilateral ceasefires beginning 
in june 1988 and the insurgents tacitly accepted the truce 
both sides claim they have respected the ceasefires 
