dissolved congress after being sworn in as president and has said 
national elections will be held may 1 
gen stroessner who ruled paraguay for 34 years fled to brazil 
where he is living in exile 
there were reports that as many as 300 people were killed during 
the coup but rodriguez has said the casualties including dead and 
wounded did not exceed 50 
montanaros flight on the brazilian airline varig left asuncion 
saturday after a twohour delay blamed on a false bomb threat 
he was accompanied by his wife martha his children augusto and 
silvia and the honduran ambassador to paraguay roberto suazo tome 
the honduran government of president jose azcona hoyo made no 
comment on montanaros arrival 
